{{Infobox Union |name= DSR/DNO |country= [[Denmark]] |affiliation= [[FTF – Confederation of Professionals in Denmark|FTF]], [[Public Services International|PSI]] |members= 74,000 (2006) |full_name= Danish Nurses' Organization |native_name= Dansk Sygeplejeråd |image= [[File:The Danish Nurses' Organization Logo.svg|180px]] |founded= 1899 |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Copenhagen]], Denmark |people= Grete Christensen, president |website= [http://www.dsr.dk/PortalPage.aspx?MenuItemID=265 www.dsr.dk] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. --> The '''Danish Nurses' Organization''' ([[Abbreviation|abbrev]]. '''DNO'''; in [[Danish language|Danish]] ''Dansk Sygeplejeråd'', abbrev. ''DSR'') is a [[trade union]] in [[Denmark]]. It represents 95% of all [[nurse]]s with a membership of 75,000.
